com.google.api.client.googleapis.subscriptions

Interface NotificationCallback

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    JsonNotificationCallback, MockNotificationCallback, TypedNotificationCallback
    Deprecated. 
    (scheduled to be removed in 1.17) Use UnparsedNotificationCallback instead.

    @Deprecated
public interface NotificationCallback
extends java.io.Serializable
    Beta
    Callback which is used to receive UnparsedNotifications after subscribing to a topic.

    Must not be implemented in form of an anonymous class as this will break serialization.

    Should be thread-safe as several notifications might be processed at the same time.

    State will only be persisted once when a subscription is created. All state changes occurring during the .handleNotification(..) call will be lost.

    Example usage: 
        class MyNotificationCallback extends NotificationCallback {
      void handleNotification(
          Subscription subscription, UnparsedNotification notification) {
         if (notification.getEventType().equals(EventTypes.UPDATED)) {
          // add items in the notification to the local client state ...
        }
      }
    }

    ...

    myRequest.subscribe(new MyNotificationCallback()).execute();
    Since:
    1.14
    Author:
    Matthias Linder (mlinder)
